Overview of the IRK-SINDy framework: (a) For each benchmark problem, we perform measurements that incorporate noise and, thereafter form a dataset. Our objective is to construct a model that is parsimonious, interpretable, and possesses generalizability, capable of accurately forecasting reference dynamics. (b) Given an appropriate initial guess (e.g., \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
