Overview of the deep IRK-SINDy framework: (a) The dataset is prepared for the purpose of training the neural network. (b) The inputs to the neural network are assigned into two distinct variables: time and state variables. The neurons located in the output layer of the network are partitioned into s segments, each containing d neurons. The i’th segment predicts the d stage values corresponding to the \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
